SUMMARY:Napa Valley StreamFest
DESCRIPTION:April 24 & 25\, 2026\nPURCHASE TICKETS HERE  \nProgram starts: 10:30am\nAge: 18+ \nNapa Valley StreamFest is back\, reimagining the film festival experience.  Join us Friday and Saturday for an immersive journey through world-premiere film screenings\, live podcast recordings\, “unfiltered” conversations with creators\, and our renowned StreamFest Tribute Awards. \n\nWe’ve fixed the festival model: One curated stage. No lines. No venue hopping. Just storytelling at its finest. \nChoose Your Experience: \nThe 2-Day Experience ($225): The Ultimate Bingeable Weekend at Uptown Theatre  \nFriday\, April 24th \n\nOn-stage conversation with Amanda McCants\, moderated by Mark S. Allen\nAM Binge: Micro-shorts\, Drama Block\, and a Pilot Episode\nAn afternoon break at the SABU Wellness Experience with Dr. Jenelle Kim at the CIA at Copia. Panel discussion with JB Copland\, Chrisspy and Katherine Castro\nPM Binge: Live Podcasts (TBD) & the “Females In Focus” Shorts Block presented by the Association of Women Directors\nFriday Night Double Feature: Marquee Film (TBD) + If These Walls Could Rock with director Tyler Measom and special guest\n\nSaturday\, April 25th  \n\nOn-stage conversation with comedian Becky Robinson\, moderated by Mark S. Allen\nAM Binge: “StreamFest In The Works” pitch competition\, Shorts Comedy Block\, and announcement of the Big Short Competition\nAn afternoon break with pop-up panels\, book signings\, and conversations at local downtown locations\, all within blocks from Uptown Theatre\nPM Binge: Pilot Episodes and Short Films\nStreamFest Tribute Awards with special guests\nAwards Chatter Live Podcast with Scott Feinberg from The Hollywood Reporter\, featuring a celebrity guest\nSaturday Night World-Premiere feature film: Casa Grande\n\nSingle-Day Passes (Friday or Saturday) for just $125\n\n \n4-DAY VIP experiences are also available\, which include the Thursday Opening Night “Push Play” Party\, additional panel discussions\, and the Sunday “Hit Pause” Party.\n \nStreamFest is a 501(c)3 Non-profit supporting mid-career professionals pivoting into or within the entertainment industry. Join our mission in supporting storytelling across all streaming platforms. Passes are going fast; secure your seat now.\n \nTickets at https://Napavalleystreamfest2026.eventbrite.com\n 
URL:https://www.uptowntheatrenapa.com/event/napa-valley-streamfest-4/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.uptowntheatrenapa.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/StreamFest-AD-2-12.png
END:VEVENT
